\par Telepathic Bond
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Divination
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  You plus one willing creature per three levels, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You forge a telepathic bond among yourself and a number o
f willing creatures, each of which must have an Intelligence score of 3 or higher. Each creature included in the link is linked to all the others. The creatures can communicate telepathically through the bond regardless of language. No special power or in
fluence is established as a result of the bond. Once the bond is formed, it works over any distance (although not from one plane to another).
\par If desired, you may leave yourself out of the telepathic bond forged. This decision must be made at the time of casting.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Telepathic bond }{\fs20\cf0 can be made permanent with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency }{\fs20\cf0 spell, though it only bonds two creatures per casting of }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 Pieces of eggshell from two different kinds of creatures.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Teleport
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Teleportation)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5, Travel 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal and touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You and touched objects or other touched willing creatures
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None and Will negates (object)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No and Yes (object)
\par This spell instantly transports you to a designated destination, which may be as distant as 100 miles per caster level. Interplanar travel is not possible. You can bring along objects as long as their weight doesn\rquote t exceed your maximum
 load. You may also bring one additional willing Medium or smaller creature (carrying gear or objects up to its maximum load) or its equivalent (see below) per three caster levels. A Large creature counts as two Medium creatures, a Huge creature counts as
 
two Large creatures, and so forth. All creatures to be transported must be in contact with one another, and at least one of those creatures must be in contact with you. As with all spells where the range is personal and the target is you, you need not mak
e a saving throw, nor is spell resistance applicable to you. Only objects held or in use (attended) by another person receive saving throws and spell resistance.
\par You must have some clear idea of the location and layout of the destination. The clearer your mental image, the more likely the teleportation works. Areas of strong physical or magical energy may make teleportation more hazardous or even impossible.

\par To see how well the teleportation works, roll d% and consult the Teleport table. Refer to the following information for definitions of the terms on the table.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Familiarity: }{\fs20\cf0 \'93Very familiar\'94 is a place where you have been very often and where you feel at home. \'93Studied carefully\'94 is a place you know well, either because you can currently see it, you\rquote ve been 
there often, or you have used other means (such as }{\i\fs20\cf0 scrying}{\fs20\cf0 ) to study the place for at least one hour. \'93Seen casually\'94 is a place that you have seen more than once but with which you are not very familiar. \'93Viewed once
\'94 is a place that you have seen once, possibly using magic. 
\par \'93False destination\'94 is a place that does not truly exist or if you are teleporting to an otherwise familiar location that no longer exists as such or has been so completely altered as to no longer be familiar to you. When traveling to
 a false destination, roll 1d20+80 to obtain results on the table, rather than rolling d%, since there is no real destination for you to hope to arrive at or even be off target from.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 On Target: }{\fs20\cf0 You appear where you want to be.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Off Target: }{\fs20\cf0 You appear safely a random distance away from the destination in a random direction. Distance off target is 1d10x1d10% of the distance that was to be traveled. The direction off target is determined randomly
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Similar Area: }{\fs20\cf0 You wind up in an area that\rquote s visually or thematically similar to the target area.
\par Generally, you appear in the closest similar place within range. If no such area exists within the spell\rquote s range, the spell simply fails instead.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Mishap: }{\fs20\cf0 You and anyone else teleporting with you have gotten \'93scrambled.\'94 You each take 1d10 points of damage, and you reroll on the chart to see where you wind up. For these rerolls, roll 1d20+80. Each time \'93Mishap\'94
 comes up, the characters take more damage and must reroll.
