\par You create a circle on the floor or other horizontal surface that teleports, as }{\i\fs20\cf0 greater teleport, }{\fs20\cf0 any creature who stands on it to a designated spot. Once you designate the destination for the circle, you can\rquote 
t change it. The spell fails if you attempt to set the circle to teleport creatures into a solid object, to a place with which you are not familiar and have no clear description, or to another plane.
\par The circle itself is subtle and nearly impossible to notice. If you intend to keep creatures from activating it accidentally, you need to mark the circle in some way.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Teleportation circle }{\fs20\cf0 can be made permanent with a }{\i\fs20\cf0 permanency }{\fs20\cf0 spell. A permanent }{\i\fs20\cf0 teleportation circle }{\fs20\cf0 
that is disabled becomes inactive for 10 minutes, then can be triggered again as normal.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Note: }{\fs20\cf0 Magic traps such as }{\i\fs20\cf0 teleportation circle }{\fs20\cf0 are hard to detect and disable. A rogue
 (only) can use the Search skill to find the circle and Disable Device to thwart it. The DC in each case is 25 + spell level, or 34 in the case of }{\i\fs20\cf0 teleportation circle}{\fs20\cf0 .
