\par This spell seems to make time cease to flow for everyone but you. In fact, you speed up so greatly that all other creatures seem
 frozen, though they are actually still moving at their normal speeds. You are free to act for 1d4+1 rounds of apparent time. Normal and magical fire, cold, gas, and the like can still harm you. While the }{\i\fs20\cf0 time stop }{\fs20\cf0 
is in effect, other creatures are invulnerable to your attacks and spells; you cannot target such creatures with any attack or spell. A spell that affects an area and has a duration longer than the remaining duration of the }{\i\fs20\cf0 time stop}{
\fs20\cf0  have their normal effects on other creatures once the }{\i\fs20\cf0 time stop }{\fs20\cf0 ends. Most spellcasters use the additional time to improve their defenses, summon allies, or flee from combat.
\par You cannot move or harm items held, carried, or worn by a creature stuck in normal time, but you can affect any item that is not in another creature\rquote s possession.
\par You are undetectable while }{\i\fs20\cf0 time stop }{\fs20\cf0 lasts. You cannot enter an area protected by an }{\i\fs20\cf0 antimagic field }{\fs20\cf0 while under the effect of }{\i\fs20\cf0 time stop.
