\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M/DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Up to two 10-ft. cubes/level (S)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Permanent; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  See text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par This spell turns natural, uncut or unworked rock of any sort
 into an equal volume of mud. Magical stone is not affected by the spell. The depth of the mud created cannot exceed 10 feet. A creature unable to levitate, fly, or otherwise free itself from the mud sinks until hip- or chest-deep, reducing its speed to 5
 feet and causing a \endash 2 penalty on attack rolls and AC. Brush thrown atop the mud can support creatures able to climb on top of it. Creatures large enough to walk on the bottom can wade through the area at a speed of 5 feet.
\par If }{\i\fs20\cf0 transmute rock to mud }{\fs20\cf0 is cast 
upon the ceiling of a cavern or tunnel, the mud falls to the floor and spreads out in a pool at a depth of 5 feet. The falling mud and the ensuing cave-in deal 8d6 points of bludgeoning damage to anyone caught directly beneath the area, or half damage to 
those who succeed on Reflex saves.
\par Castles and large stone buildings are generally immune to the effect of the spell, since }{\i\fs20\cf0 transmute rock to mud }{\fs20\cf0 can\rquote t affect worked stone and doesn\rquote t reach deep enough to undermine such buildings\rquote 
 foundations. However, small buildings or structures often rest upon foundations shallow enough to be damaged or even partially toppled by this spell.
\par The mud remains until a successful }{\i\fs20\cf0 dispel magic }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\i\fs20\cf0 transmute mud to rock }{\fs20\cf0 spell restores its substance\emdash but not necessarily its form. 
Evaporation turns the mud to normal dirt over a period of days. The exact time depends on exposure to the sun, wind, and normal drainage.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Arcane Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 Clay and water.
\par 
