\par This spell creates a wall of rock that merges into adjoining rock surfaces. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 wall of stone }{\fs20\cf0 is 1 inch thick per four caster levels and composed of up to one 5-foot square per level. You can double the wall\rquote 
s area by halving its thickness. The wall cannot be conjured so that it occupies the same space as a creature or another object.
\par Unlike a }{\i\fs20\cf0 wall of iron, }{\fs20\cf0 you can create a }{\i\fs20\cf0 wall of stone }{\fs20\cf0 in almost any shape you desire. The wall created need not be ver
tical, nor rest upon any firm foundation; however, it must merge with and be solidly supported by existing stone. It can be used to bridge a chasm, for instance, or as a ramp. For this use, if the span is more than 20 feet, the wall must be arched and but
tressed. This requirement reduces the spell\rquote s area by half. The wall can be crudely shaped to allow crenellations, battlements, and so forth by likewise reducing the area.
\par Like any other stone wall, this one can be destroyed by a }{\i\fs20\cf0 disintegrate }{\fs20\cf0 spell or by no
rmal means such as breaking and chipping. Each 5-foot square of the wall has 15 hit points per inch of thickness and hardness 8. A section of wall whose hit points drop to 0 is breached. If a creature tries to break through the wall with a single attack, 
the DC for the Strength check is 20 + 2 per inch of thickness.
\par It is possible, but difficult, to trap mobile opponents within or under a }{\i\fs20\cf0 wall of stone}{\fs20\cf0 , provided the wall is shaped so it can hold the creatures. Creatures can avoid entrapment with successful Reflex saves.
